
  <sn><md>### The Anglo-Saxon Age {.text-center}

Origins, Culture, and Literary Foundations

The **Anglo-Saxon Age**, often referred to as the `Old English` period or the `Dark Age`, serves as the `starting point for British literature`. Spanning approximately from ++450 AD to 1066 AD++ (with some scholars noting its beginning as early as `410 AD`), this era laid the foundational structures of the English language, culture, and governance.
</md></sn>
